---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout
  title="Legal &amp; privacy · VTourn"
  description="Terms of use, privacy policy, cookie policy, and our position on real-money play."
  ogImage="/og/legal.png"
>
  <article class="container-prose pt-16 pb-16 prose-vt">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white">Legal &amp; privacy</h1>
    <p class="text-ink-500 text-sm mt-2">Last updated: 9 May 2026 (placeholder — full v1 lands before public launch).</p>

    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>VTourn is a project incubated by Growth Spurt Limited and operating under the working name "VTourn Holdings" pending Foundation incorporation per <a href="https://github.com/0800tim/vtorn/blob/main/docs/19-open-source-and-contributor-revenue.md" class="link">doc 19</a>.</p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The handle you sign in with (Telegram username, Discord username, email, etc.).</li>
      <li>Predictions you submit, with timestamps.</li>
      <li>Device coarse geo (country only, derived from your IP at our edge).</li>
      <li>Hashed IP and user-agent for bot-detection. We never store raw IPs or raw user-agents.</li>
      <li>Optional: an Ethereum address for Drips Network payouts.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we don't collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Your phone number, unless you opt into the Telegram or WhatsApp bot.</li>
      <li>Your real name, unless you provide it.</li>
      <li>Browser fingerprint signals beyond the user-agent hash above.</li>
      <li>Any payment details. We don't process payments.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies and tracking</h2>
    <p>We use first-party cookies for session continuity. We load Google Tag Manager and (when configured) GA4 / Meta Pixel via GTM, only after you accept the consent banner. Server-side analytics events fire either way but are anonymised when consent isn't given.</p>

    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Cloudflare — DNS, edge, tunnel.</li>
      <li>Google Analytics 4 + Tag Manager — opt-in.</li>
      <li>Meta Pixel — opt-in.</li>
      <li>Drips Network — quarterly contributor payouts (pull, not push).</li>
      <li>Telegram, Discord, Apple, Google, WhatsApp Business — auth and messaging on your explicit opt-in.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Real-money play</h2>
    <p><strong>VTourn does not handle real-money pools as part of the v0.1 product.</strong> The platform tracks predictions, scores, and rankings only. Where syndicate hosts run a real-money pool among their members, those funds are held and disbursed by the host directly between participants — VTourn is not a party to the transaction.</p>
    <p>Phase 2 brings on-chain audited prize pools (per <a href="https://github.com/0800tim/vtorn/blob/main/docs/21-onchain-sweepstakes-oracle.md" class="link">doc 21</a>) gated on a passing external smart-contract audit. We will not enable on-chain prize-pool participation for users in jurisdictions where it would be regulated as gambling.</p>

    <h2>Data subject rights</h2>
    <p>You can request export or deletion of your data at any time via <code>DELETE /v1/me</code> on the API or by emailing <a href="mailto:privacy@vtourn.com" class="link">privacy@vtourn.com</a>. Predictions are retained as anonymised aggregates after deletion to preserve historical leaderboard integrity, but no PII is kept.</p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>Disclosures: <a href="mailto:security@vtourn.com" class="link">security@vtourn.com</a>. We commit to acknowledging within 48 hours and patching within 14 days for high-severity issues. Bounties are paid from the strategic-reserve fund per <a href="https://github.com/0800tim/vtorn/blob/main/docs/19-open-source-and-contributor-revenue.md" class="link">doc 19</a>.</p>

    <h2>Licences</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Code: Apache 2.0.</li>
      <li>Docs: CC-BY 4.0.</li>
      <li>Player photographs: Wikimedia Commons under their respective CC-BY-SA terms; full attribution at <a href="https://github.com/0800tim/vtorn/blob/main/apps/web/public/CREDITS.md" class="link">CREDITS.md</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>General: <a href="mailto:hello@vtourn.com" class="link">hello@vtourn.com</a>. Privacy: <a href="mailto:privacy@vtourn.com" class="link">privacy@vtourn.com</a>. Security: <a href="mailto:security@vtourn.com" class="link">security@vtourn.com</a>. Partners: <a href="mailto:partners@vtourn.com" class="link">partners@vtourn.com</a>.</p>
  </article>
</Layout>
